cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper introduces a new end-to-end text-to-speech (E2E-TTS) toolkit, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the scope of cs.CL.
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speech processing and specifically on generating speech from text, which falls under the scope of cs.SD.
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper discusses various E2E-TTS models and their performance, which involves signal processing techniques and falls under the scope of cs.SI.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper describes the design of the toolkit and experimental evaluation of the models, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the scope of cs.LG.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the integration of ASR functions with TTS, which involves control systems and falls under the scope of cs.SY.
